summary: Imagine being a teen Avenger and Tony taking care of you when you're stressed about your...
body:
Imagine being a teen Avenger and Tony taking care of you when you’re stressed about your studies.

[x] // requester: anonymous // request: here

There always came a time in the year when your whole body asked you for a break yet you had to keep on working. Your eyes would slowly become bloodshot; one of your pupils a jagged mess, seemingly piercing through the iris into the sclera. It moved every now and then to a beat only it could hear.

You bit your tongue while you wrote down your notes, trying not to argue with the low growl now creeping through your mind.

You were also suffering from a thing called stress. See, things can easily go wrong when people are stressed. And, well, let’s say you were under stress constantly, causing you to lose your focus during missions or meetings. Everyone seemed to ignore the fact that you were under so much pressure. Everyone but Tony.

Tony was always there for you. He was like a father to you. So whenever he saw you like this, his heart ached. One night, casually strolling along the hall of the compound, Tony spotted you struggling with your studies. He stopped in his tracks and, with a weary look, sighed.

“Hey, what have I told you about staying up so late?” he scolded, getting your attention.

“I know, I know but I have an exam next week,” you answered.

He walked over to the table you were sitting by and peeked over your shoulder at your books – Thermonuclear astrophysics. “Who’s giving you this class?”

“Agent Phil Coulson. They say he’s tough,” you breathed, throwing yourself down.

“Tough? Sweetheart, Coulson is anything but that. Besides,” he began trying to meet your gaze; “no one compares to you,” he said, pointing at you. “Come on, I think you should get some rest,” he said putting a hand on your shoulder.

“Are you sure?” you asked, yawning.

Looking at you and your evident lack of sleep, he nodded. “Uh…yup. I can give you a hand with this tomorrow. Okay?”

“Okay.”

summary: A Mom’s reaction to the MCU/Infinity War
title: A Mom’s reaction to the MCU/Infinity War
body: So over the past month and a half, I decided to sit down with my mom and watch almost all the Marvel movies leading up to Infinity War (Don’t have Ant-Man and the Wasp yet). At first I was expecting just to get to Avengers, due to her not really liking super hero movies. But to her surprise and mine, she was enjoying them. She fell in love with the characters, laughed and talked about them too. Today we watched Infinity War and she went in with no clue what was about to happen. I told her that almost all of the characters from the MCU were in this movie and see was excited. Then the Snap happened. When she realized what was happening, she started to cry and almost begged me to turn the movie off. I never seen her react like that to any movie we seen. She lost it when Groot died, and don’t get me started on Spider-Man. Our road for movies end here for now, but we are preparing to watch Ant-Man and the Wasp soon just before Captain Marvel, so she can experience the true hype of watching these movies with a crowd. This is just the beginning
